3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates BLUR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding fee is exchanged directly between long and short position holders, with no commission taken by Bybit. Rates are typically capped at ±2% per funding interval, providing predictable maximum exposure for arbitrage strategies."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to NFT market sentiment creates distinct funding rate patterns compared to DeFi or Layer 1 tokens. The token's lower liquidity compared to major cryptocurrencies can lead to more pronounced funding rate deviations, particularly during NFT market cycles. These characteristics make BLUR/USDT suitable for traders seeking alternatives to overcrowded BTC/ETH funding arbitrage opportunities."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown correlation with NFT trading volume spikes and OpenSea activity. During Q1 2023's NFT market revival, funding rates frequently exceeded +1% as retail traders took long positions expecting continued momentum. Conversely, during NFT market downturns, negative funding rates of -0.5% to -1% have been observed as traders short the token. The 8-hour funding cycle allows for multiple arbitrage entries per day when rate deviations persist across cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Successful BLUR/USDT funding arbitrage requires monitoring both Bybit's perpetual rates and spot market availability across exchanges like Binance and OKX. The token's moderate liquidity means larger arbitrage positions may experience slippage when hedging in spot markets. Cross-exchange spreads typically range from 0.1-0.5%, which must be factored into profitability calculations alongside Bybit's 0.055% maker fees. Automated strategies should account for BLUR's tendency toward gap movements during major NFT announcements."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Factors"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's volatility can exceed 20% daily during NFT market events, requiring careful position sizing and stop-loss management beyond standard funding rate arbitrage approaches. The token's correlation with ETH means hedging strategies should consider broader crypto market movements, particularly during periods of high ETH volatility. Bybit's unified trading account helps manage margin efficiently, but traders should maintain adequate buffers for BLUR's unpredictable price action. Weekend funding periods may show different patterns due to reduced NFT trading activity."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical BLUR/USDT funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"BLUR/USDT funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.3% to +0.8% per 8-hour period during normal market conditions. During NFT market excitement or significant protocol updates, rates can reach the ±2% cap, creating substantial arbitrage opportunities for prepared traders."},{"question":"How does Bybit's BLUR perpetual compare to other exchanges?","answer":"Bybit offers competitive BLUR/USDT funding rates with reliable 8-hour cycles and strong technical infrastructure. While Binance may have higher BLUR spot liquidity, Bybit's derivatives-focused platform often provides more consistent rate calculations and faster execution for funding arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"What minimum capital is needed for BLUR funding arbitrage on Bybit?","answer":"Effective BLUR funding arbitrage on Bybit typically requires $5,000-10,000 minimum due to the token's volatility and spread considerations. Smaller positions may not generate sufficient returns after accounting for trading fees, hedging costs, and the capital required to weather BLUR's price swings."},{"question":"How do NFT market cycles affect BLUR funding rates?","answer":"BLUR funding rates often correlate with NFT trading volume and marketplace competition dynamics. During high-volume NFT periods, funding rates tend toward positive territory as traders anticipate BLUR token demand, while NFT market lulls frequently produce negative rates as sentiment shifts bearish."}]}]
